# Dallas bottling plant — deployment config ownership.
#
# This file is the single source of truth for who must review a change to the Dallas deployment
# configuration. GitHub enforces it on pull requests; Deployment Studio *renders* it read-only on
# the Access tab (`studio serve` → Access), so an author can see who a config change will require
# before opening the PR. The Studio never invents an approval lane — it only surfaces these rules.
#
# Rules are last-match-wins, so the site-wide catch-all is narrowed by the more specific lines.

# The whole Dallas site falls to the deployment leads unless a more specific rule applies —
# this covers definition.yaml, the bindings, and anything not called out below.
/sites/dallas-site/                                          @bottles-r-us/dallas-deploy-leads

# Scope layers carry the enterprise/site/line context merged into every component; a change here
# ripples across the plant, so config governance owns them.
/sites/dallas-site/layers/scopes/                            @bottles-r-us/config-governance

# The config-component provider wiring (how config is delivered on HOST) is platform-owned.
/sites/dallas-site/layers/provider/                          @bottles-r-us/edge-platform

# Per-line component configuration is owned by that line's controls engineers.
/sites/dallas-site/layers/components/filling-line/           @bottles-r-us/filling-line-controls
/sites/dallas-site/layers/components/packaging-line/         @bottles-r-us/packaging-line-controls

# The operator console configuration is owned by the plant-ops UI team.
/sites/dallas-site/layers/components/site/edge-console.json  @bottles-r-us/plant-ops-ui
